        {
          "name": "path",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The two-dimensional path forming the basis of the shape."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "extrusionDepth",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The thickness of the extruded shape along the z-axis."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A shape geometry."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "SceneKit determines the filled area of the path using the even-odd winding rule (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Winding Rules",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Cocoa/Conceptual/CocoaDrawingGuide/Paths/Paths.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40003290-CH206-BAJIJJGD"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Cocoa Drawing Guide",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Cocoa/Conceptual/CocoaDrawingGuide/Introduction/Introduction.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40003290"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") and extrudes this area to create a three-dimensional geometry. The result of extruding a self-intersecting path is undefined."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The extruded shape is centered at the zero point of its z-axis. For example, an extrusion depth of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "1.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " creates a shape that extends from "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "-0.5"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0.5"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " along the z-axis. An extrusion depth of zero creates a flat, one-sided shape."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The path’s flatness (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsbezierpath/1520676-flatness"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsbezierpath"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") determines the level of detail SceneKit uses in building a three-dimensional shape from the path. A larger flatness value results in fewer polygons to render, increasing performance, and a smaller flatness value increases the smoothness of curves at a cost to performance."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
